The Aga Khan Academy Mombasa has adopted an electronic examination assessment platform e-Assessment to evaluate the school. This, it says, will eliminate courier costs, leakages and losses in transit. The online exam platform will test students abilities, improve their skills and level of attentiveness. With this new system, we have achieved a guarantee of these basics, in a deployment of new technology that can, in time, render to history the problems associated with printing and distributing hard copy exam papers, Aga Khan Academy Head, Bill O Hearn said.The platform was launched at the school in June.